[Universal masking and adequate ventilation with fresh air are the simpler yet proven to be effective measures that can make a difference, if they are 'adopted' and implemented . Adoption of these measures requires a behavioural change; 'buy in' by the community at large. This requires an understanding of human psyche for effective health communication and developing information/health messages that can promote and sustain the change. - Mod.UBA]

